{subhead}Elbox : Spider - USB 2.0 Host Controller{def}
{left}
{pp}
(12/9/02)
{pp}
Elbox Computer is proud to introduce the first USB 2.0 host
controller for the Amiga computers. The Spider USB 2.0 PCI card
provides a simple and affordable way to add five Hi-Speed USB ports
to Mediator-equipped Amigas.
{pp}
The Spider USB 2.0 Hi-Speed PCI controller is backward-compatible,
which means it works also with older USB 1.1 peripherals.
{pp}
Features:{p}
• Four external and one internal USB 2.0 Hi-Speed ports{p}
• Compatible with both USB 2.0 (480 Mbps) and USB 1.1 (12 Mbps) devices{p}
• Compliant with EHCI, OHCI and PCI 2.2 standards{p}
• All ports can handle high-speed, full-speed and low-speed transaction{p}
• Supports up to 127 downstream USB devices{p}
• Supplies 500 mA power to each USB port{p}
• Supports PCI-Bus Power Management Interface{p}
• Hot Plug Capability
{pp}
Requirements:{p}
• One free PCI slot{p}
• Mediator Multimedia CD
{pp}
The package contents:{p}
• Spider USB 2.0 High-Speed PCI card{p}
• Mediator OHCI USB drivers for the Poseidon stack{p}
• Unregistered, time-limited version of the Poseidon USB stack
{pp}
Available from Sept 16 for EUR 39.95
{pp}
{link http://elbox.com/buy.html}http://elbox.com/buy.html{end}
{pp}